    "Historically, snowfall has ranged widely.",
    "For example, the winter of 2009-2010 saw a record 36.9 inches of snow in February alone, while other years have had significantly less.",
    "The city's snow removal budget has fluctuated accordingly, with millions allocated each year for snow and ice removal.",
    "Additionally, the impact of snow on the city's infrastructure and daily life can be substantial, leading to school closures and delays in public transportation.",
    "Climate change may also affect future snowfall patterns, making historical data less predictive."
